<h2 id="elements">Elements</h2>

<h3 id="back">Back</h3>

<p><a href="/" class="link-back">Back</a></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;a href="/" class="link-back"&gt;Back&lt;/a&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<h4 id="using-the-back-link">Using the back link</h4>

<p>The back link takes users back to the previous page. It should be used for transactional pages, such as an online form.</p>

<p>The back link shouldn’t be used instead of <a href="/">breadcrumbs</a></p>

<h3 id="buttons">Buttons</h3>

<p><a class="button button-start" href="financial-assessment-eligibility" role="button">Start now</a></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;a class="button button-start" href="financial-assessment-eligibility" role="button"&gt;Start now&lt;/a&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><input type="submit" class="button" value="Continue" /></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;input type="submit" class="button" value="Continue"&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<h4 id="using-buttons">Using buttons</h4>

<p>Buttons should be used to help users carry out a task, like starting an application.</p>

<p>Button text should be written in sentence case and clearly tell the user what the action is. For example, ‘Start now’, ‘Continue’, ‘Subscribe’.</p>

<p>Buttons can be used to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Start a form</li>
  <li>Continue to the next question of a form</li>
  <li>Subscribe to something, such as email notifications</li>
</ul>

<p>Buttons shouldn’t be used to replace links within the body of a page.</p>

